President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in American Samoa and ordered Federal assistance to support recovery efforts in areas affected by the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration makes federal funding available to the territory and certain nonprofit organizations for emergency protective measures. Robert J. Fenton has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on assessments and requests from the territory. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.